154
00:19:33,440 --> 00:19:35,960
Mariusz Zawydzki, Physics

155
00:22:23,200 --> 00:22:25,160
Eleven... Twenty-three...
Forty-five...

156
00:22:27,480 --> 00:22:29,920
Eleven... Twenty-three...
Forty-five...

157
00:24:27,480 --> 00:24:28,360
Oh, I forgot

158
00:24:29,400 --> 00:24:34,120
Mother phoned
She wants her umbrella and shawl

159
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:35,680
Why don't they sell shawls in shops
where she is?

160
00:24:37,160 --> 00:24:38,960
Don't you know her?
She wants to have her own one

161
00:24:39,760 --> 00:24:40,680
When is the plane due?

162
00:24:40,840 --> 00:24:42,440
At twelve, a few minutes past

163
00:24:43,280 --> 00:24:45,360
I don't operate until the afternoon
I may go to the airport,

164
00:24:45,440 --> 00:24:46,360
I'm free for an hour

165
00:24:48,440 --> 00:24:49,440
You're a dear

166
00:24:51,320 --> 00:24:52,040
Oh, give me the key

167
00:24:56,760 --> 00:24:58,640
The umbrella is on the coat-stand
